<br>
Europa Universalis is originally a french boardgame much more complex than the PC version from Paradox. The creator of the boardgame since started his own company (Galilea) and developed Pax Romana, a game destined to let you in control of a political faction during the roman republic (read twice, not empire, republic). The game seems to be really interesting.<br>
<br>
Koliandrah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maladominus>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ak'Anon Sex Symbol</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/20/03 7:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2082.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   victoria</span><hr size=1> Yep Koliandrah, <br>
<br>
Pax Romana I heard about... it's probably a game I would eventually try out. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
I do like Greco-Roman history.... I even took 2 semesters of Latin during college, even tho it was never required of me.  But for some reason, as far as strategy games go....I tend to gravitate directly towards the &quot;world conquest&quot; games.  <br>
<br>
I already decided that my next PC historico-strategy wargame is going to be Victoria!  Maybe after I finish that, I will try out Pax Romana. <br>
<br>
<br>
P.S. --- Victoria named after Queen Victoria.  Global historical conquest, colonization, world diplomacy, supremacy.  You can be almost any major nation of that era!  You can be Great Britain.  You can be France.  You can be the Czar of all the Russias.  You can be Imperial China under the last dynasty of the Manchu Emperors. Or you can be the Prussian Empire trying to unite yourself into Greater Germany.  Or you can be the ailing and struggling Ottoman Empire.  You can be Tokugawa Japan.  You can be the USA.  And you can even play as the Confederate States of America....whereupon you aim for a military alliance with France or Britain in order to gang up on the Union!  Hah!  You can also play the Lone Star Republic.... tho I doubt it has much chance of surviving in a long campaign game.  <br>
